Feature: The FES second swarm stands up as a 2-pack with proven Telegram separation and a distinct fleet identity

# BL-439 (feature/runbook, epic BL-435 slice 4 — the epic's E2E acceptance, PARKED behind BL-436+BL-437):
# turn "fleet of one, in theory" into "fleet of two, for real". A runbook stands up a real second swarm
# against free-email-scanner (local repo C:\Users\Carillon\source\repos\free-email-scanner) as a 2-pack
# (the 15GB host holds ONE full swarm, so FES is minimal), launched from the Windows-side swarmforge
# checkout (target on /mnt/c, where Linux-side tmux sockets are unreliable), with its own bot+group. The
# forcing-function acceptance: the FES swarm's inbound never steals the primary's (Telegram separation,
# per BL-436), and both swarms appear as distinct identities in the fleet console (per BL-437). Scenarios
# live in this .feature.draft until BL-436 + BL-437 land and this ticket is promoted.
#
# Scope (verify at build time): a runbook under docs/ for the FES 2-pack bring-up, plus the E2E
# acceptance that exercises BL-436 (per-swarm creds) and BL-437 (fleet status publish) against a real
# second swarm. This slice also exercises the full onboarding ceremony end to end (BL-262/344/380/381/382)
# as its real-world acceptance.

Background:
  Given the primary swarm is running with its own bot and group

# BL-439 fes-second-swarm-bringup-01
Scenario: Following the runbook stands up the FES swarm as a 2-pack with its own swarm_name
  When the FES bring-up runbook is followed
  Then a second swarm named "fes" runs as a 2-pack
  And it is launched from the Windows-side checkout against the /mnt/c target

# BL-439 fes-second-swarm-bringup-02
Scenario: The FES swarm resolves its own bot token from its fleet creds file
  Given the FES swarm has its own fleet creds file
  When the FES front desk resolves its Telegram creds
  Then it uses the FES bot token, not the primary's

# BL-439 fes-second-swarm-bringup-03
Scenario: Neither swarm's inbound is consumed by the other
  Given both the primary and FES swarms are polling their own bots
  When a message is sent to the primary's bot
  Then the FES swarm does not consume it
  And when a message is sent to the FES bot the primary swarm does not consume it

# BL-439 fes-second-swarm-bringup-04
Scenario: Both swarms appear as distinct identities in the fleet console
  Given both the primary and FES swarms publish their status.json
  When the fleet console reads the fleet
  Then it renders the primary and "fes" as two distinct swarms
